Walked in this morning for some mangu (tres golpes - Dominican breakfast) and was extremely dissatisfied.For a small order for $5, I was given just one small egg, about the size of a quail egg, that looked like someone had taken a bite of it already. The mangu had good seasoning and flavor but was literally DRIPPING in oil. A soupy mess. I had to dab paper towels all around it just so it could be edible. It came with just one sausage round which tasted good, and the onions were good as well. However she gave me NO FRIED CHEESE at all. Service seemed fine, they spoke English and Spanish until I saw a worker in the back mashing up more mangu with her bare hands. Her hands could have been clean but for the large quantities she was mashing up, she should have used gloves honestly. Then that same woman came to ring me up, with mangu all over her hands, and handed me my debit card with mangu and oil all over it and didn’t seem to think that was an issue. Won’t be coming back.
